---
export interface Props {}
---

<style>
  :root {
    --primary: #fff;
    --background: #f8f6f3;
    --text: #fff;
    --accent: #fff;
    --highlight-bg: #fff4f0;
    --table-bg: #fff;
    --table-alt-bg: #fdf2f2;
  }
  .exceptional-section {
    background: var(--background);
    padding: 6rem 2rem;
    background-image: url('/photos/Exceptional-bg.jpg');
    background-size: cover;
    background-position: bottom;
    background-repeat: no-repeat;
    height: 1900px;
    width: 100vw;
    margin-left: calc(50% - 50vw);
    margin-right: calc(50% - 50vw);
    font-family: 'Montserrat', sans-serif;
    color: var(--text);
    display: flex;
    align-items:flex-start
  }
  .exceptional-content {
    max-width: 900px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 0 2rem;
  }
  .exceptional-heading {
    font-size: 2.75rem;
    font-weight: 800;
    color: var(--primary);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }
  .narrative-block {

    margin-bottom: 2rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
    font-size: 1.125rem;
  }
  .comparison-container {
    overflow-x: auto;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }
  .comparison-table {

    border-collapse: collapse;
  }
  .comparison-table td {
    padding: 0.5rem;
    text-align: left;
  }
  .comparison-table td:first-child {
    font-weight: 500;
  }
  .cta {

    margin-top: 4rem;
  }
  .btn-primary {
    display: inline-block;
    padding: 0.75rem 1.5rem;
    background: #000;
    color: var(--accent);
    border-radius: 0.5rem;
    text-decoration: none;
    font-weight: 600;
    transition: background 0.3s ease;
  }
  .btn-primary:hover {
    background: #800000;
  }
  @media (min-width: 640px) {
    .exceptional-heading { font-size: 3.5rem; }
    .narrative-block { font-size: 1.25rem; }
  }
</style>

<section class="exceptional-section">
  <div class="exceptional-content">
    <h2 class="exceptional-heading">Exceptional Value</h2>

    <div class="narrative-block">
      Picture this: a sleek studio in Dubai, lights humming, cameras rolling, at a price tag that could fund an entire week of shooting in Europe. Now imagine swapping that glare of skyscrapers for the tranquil peaks around Bishkek—same top-tier equipment, same seasoned crew, but with costs trimmed by more than half.
    </div>

    <div class="comparison-container">
      <table class="comparison-table">
        <tr>
          <td><strong>Expense</strong></td>
          <td><strong>Dubai</strong></td>
          <td><strong>Bishkek</strong></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Studio Day Rental</td>
          <td>$5,000</td>
          <td>$1,500</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Camera Package (per day)</td>
          <td>$1,200</td>
          <td>$350</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Crew Rate (pp/day)</td>
          <td>$2,000</td>
          <td>$500</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Post-Production Suite</td>
          <td>$3,000</td>
          <td>$900</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>Total Budget</strong></td>
          <td><strong>$100,000</strong></td>
          <td><strong>$40,000</strong></td>
        </tr>
      </table>
    </div>

    <div class="narrative-block">
      Those savings aren't just numbers—they're extra shooting days, upgraded talent, and creative freedom. In Bishkek, your vision takes front and center, not your overheads.
    </div>

    <div class="cta">
      <a href="/contact" class="btn-primary">Get Your Custom Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>